abstract: "An agent-universal Git-cloneable project scaffold that helps graduate students and researchers build, calibrate, solve, simulate, and write up structural economic models (DSGE, CGE/GTAP, heterogeneous-agent, dynamic programming) with the assistance of AI agents (Codex CLI, Claude Code, Cursor, etc.). Includes 23 task-specific skills, 6 reviewer subagent specs, 5 cross-process rules, language-agnostic templates and CLI tooling."
